# Leash — Data Model

## Entities

### Entity: Harness

The core Rust runtime library. Manages safety gates (deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate), pilot token sessions with TTL, sim vs physical drivers, and telemetry broadcast. Monolithic for now; module graph is a planned extraction.

```yaml
entity: Harness
type: entity
properties:
  role:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "robot"
  profile:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [sim, waveshare-ugv]
    default: sim
  adapters:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Feature-gated adapter list
  safety_gates:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate
  deadman_ms:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 400
    description: Auto-stop if no command within this window
  soft_odometry_limit_m:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 0.0
    description: Odometry-based travel cap; 0 means disabled
  allow_physical_actuation:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
    description: Must be true or LEASH_ALLOW_PHYSICAL_ACTUATION=1 for physical profiles
  allow_untokened_drive:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: Whether drive commands without a pilot token are accepted
states: [planned, mapped, extracted, stabilized, released]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → extracted → stabilized → released
```

### Entity: ModuleGraph

Typed module runtime. Modules declare inputs, outputs, lifecycle, health, and metadata. Streams are typed and validated at graph construction. First implementation in-process and sim-safe. Not yet extracted from the monolithic Harness.

```yaml
entity: ModuleGraph
type: entity
properties:
  module_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  stream_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  isolation:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [in_process, cross_process, network]
    default: in_process
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested, active]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested → active
```

### Entity: Blueprints

Runnable catalog of robot configs, sim scenarios, replay sessions, and agentic demos. Every demo and robot stack is a versioned, runnable blueprint. No ad-hoc wiring.

```yaml
entity: Blueprints
type: entity
properties:
  catalog:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Blueprint names (ugv-nav, sim-replay, agent-debug)
  versioned:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
states: [planned, cataloged, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → cataloged → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Transport

Abstraction layer for module communication. Works identically across in-process channels, cross-process IPC, TCP network, and ecosystem bridges (ROS2, Zenoh). Modules never know their peer's location.

```yaml
entity: Transport
type: entity
properties:
  backends:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: in-process, cross-process, tcp, bridge
  default_backend:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [in_process, cross_process, tcp]
    default: in_process
states: [planned, designed, implemented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → designed → implemented → tested
```

### Entity: Telemetry

Live telemetry streaming via broadcast channel and WebSocket. TelemetryFrame with odometry, battery, speed mode, estop, deadman, sensor snapshots. Visualization (graph views, command center) not yet built; data pipeline exists.

```yaml
entity: Telemetry
type: entity
properties:
  views:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: graph, streams, spatial, command-center
  output:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [json_stream, ws, cli, mcp]
states: [planned, implemented, active]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → active
```

### Entity: Replay

Simulation-first, deterministic replay engine. Recorded sessions reproduce identical telemetry from the same inputs. Zero hardware requirement. Core safety and debugging primitive.

```yaml
entity: Replay
type: entity
properties:
  buffer_format:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "leash-replay-v1"
  determinism:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: true
    description: Identical telemetry from same inputs
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

### Entity: CLI

Command-line interface and localhost HTTP server. Subcommands: serve (mcp|http), health, stop. Feature-gated transports. HTTP server exposes 16 REST + WebSocket endpoints.

```yaml
entity: CLI
type: entity
properties:
  listen:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "127.0.0.1:8000"
  commands:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: serve (mcp|http), health, stop
  http_endpoints:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: health, capabilities, telemetry, sensors, camera/status, capture, pilot/authorize, pilot/speed-mode, drive, motors/drive, motors/stop, estop, estop/reset, stream, ws/telemetry
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: MCPServer

MCP stdio server (rmcp crate). 7 tools exposed to local LLM clients: health, capabilities, observe, invoke_capability (authorize/drive/stop/estop/estop_reset/speed_mode), stop, estop, capture.

```yaml
entity: MCPServer
type: entity
properties:
  tools:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: health, capabilities, observe, invoke_capability, stop, estop, capture
  transport:
    type: enum
    required: true
    values: [stdio]
states: [planned, implemented, tested, released]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → tested → released
```

### Entity: UGVAdapter

Feature-gated Waveshare Ubuntu UGV hardware adapter. Serial port JSON-line protocol. Configurable drive inversion, drive swap, baud rate. Only compiles with `--features waveshare-ugv`.

```yaml
entity: UGVAdapter
type: entity
properties:
  target:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "Waveshare Ubuntu UGV"
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "waveshare-ugv"
  serial_port:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "/dev/ttyTHS1"
  serial_baud:
    type: number
    required: true
    default: 115200
  drive_invert:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
  drive_swap:
    type: boolean
    required: true
    default: false
states: [planned, implemented, feature_gated, documented]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → feature_gated → documented
```

### Entity: Bridge

Compatibility layer for existing robot bridge clients. Maps legacy APIs to the harness runtime. Feature flag `bridge-compat` exists; actual shim code not yet written.

```yaml
entity: Bridge
type: entity
properties:
  clients:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Supported bridge client list
  shim_layer:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: Compatibility shim path
states: [planned, mapped, documented, tested]
lifecycle: planned → mapped → documented → tested
```

### Entity: Safety

Runtime safety gates (deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit, physical-actuation-gate) plus smoke-test scripts for MCP, HTTP, and physical gate verification.

```yaml
entity: Safety
type: entity
properties:
  test_targets:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: MCP, HTTP, physical-gate, safety-gates (deadman, estop, soft-odometry-limit)
  feature_flag:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "smoke"
  scripts:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: smoke-http.sh, smoke-mcp.py, smoke-physical-gate.sh
states: [planned, implemented, verified]
lifecycle: planned → implemented → verified
```

### Entity: ReleasePipeline

Packages the harness for crates.io and GitHub binary releases. Cargo.toml metadata complete; CI release workflow not yet configured.

```yaml
entity: ReleasePipeline
type: entity
properties:
  targets:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: crates.io, GitHub binaries
  platforms:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: linux-x86_64, macos-arm64
states: [planned, configured, publishing]
lifecycle: planned → configured → publishing
```

### Entity: Bootstrap

Crate skeleton complete. MIT license, Cargo.toml (leash-harness 0.1.0), CI workflow at `.github/workflows/ci.yml`, repo provenance. CI has not yet passed (no green build).

```yaml
entity: Bootstrap
type: entity
properties:
  license:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "MIT"
  ci_platform:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "GitHub Actions"
  crate_name:
    type: string
    required: true
    default: "leash-harness"
  features:
    type: string
    required: true
    description: default=sim+http+mcp, waveshare-ugv, bridge-compat
states: [planned, bootstrapped, ci_green]
lifecycle: planned → bootstrapped → ci_green
```

## Relationships

### Relationship: Bootstrap → Harness

```yaml
relationship: Bootstrap → Harness
verb: provisions
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
```

